==English==
===Noun===
 
# A game that is played between two sides using between two and six colored balls but typically using four colored balls.  The object of the game is to score wickets by passing the balls through the wickets in a particular order, usually in a set pattern going in one direction and then back through them in the other direction and finally ending at the peg.  The last wicket (or hoop) is called the rover hoop and is marked with red paint.  When all balls for one side goes through all the hoops and hits the peg the game is completed and the score is determined by the number of hoops each side has scored.  Championship croquet consists of four colored balls, six wickets and one peg.

# A shot in the game of croquet whereby the striker ball is placed in contact with the roqueted ball and both balls are driven away with a strike from the mallet onto the striker ball.  Both the striker ball and the croqueted ball must move during the croquet stroke.  A variety of strokes may be played which cause the striker and croquet balls to move in various directions and distances.  These strokes include split, takeoff, drive, half-roll, full-roll and [[passroll]] shots.